"
    input clk_i,

    input  [DATA_WIDTH - 1 : 0] data_i,
    output [DATA_WIDTH - 1 : 0] data_o
"
- ports and respective bit widths are correct
[Marc103 + Codex 5.5 - 06/17/26]

"
    generate
        if(LATENCY == 0) begin
            assign data_o = data_i;
        end else begin
            logic [LATENCY : 1][DATA_WIDTH - 1 : 0] data;
"
- packed widths are correct
    - latency 0 is a direct passthrough
    - 'LATENCY : 1' is intentional for latency greater than 0, where [1]
      represents 1 cycle later, [2] represents 2 cycles later, etc.
[Marc103 + Codex 5.5 - 06/17/26]


"
            always@(posedge clk_i) begin
                data[1] <= data_i;
                for(int i = 2; i <= LATENCY; i++) begin
                    data[i] <= data[i - 1];
                end
            end

            assign data_o = data[LATENCY];
        end
    endgenerate
"
- clk_i used
- for loop conditions are correct, start at 2 -> LATENCY (inclusive)
    - [1] captures data_i directly, later stages set [i] to [i - 1]
- final assign data_o points to [LATENCY], with a direct data_i passthrough for LATENCY == 0
- all outputs assigned
[Marc103 + Codex 5.5 - 06/17/26]

